Introduction to Docker for Java Developers ( A use case driven approach )

Goal of the course: 
What is docker? Overview
Docker installation
    - Ubuntu
    - Ubuntu on Windows
    - Mac 
Basics
 1. Images 
 2. Containers
 3. Docker basic commands
  
Use case 1 : Build - > Ship - > Run an nginx instance running an html page.
Use case 2 : Build - > Ship - > Run an apache instance running an html page.    
Use case 3 : Build - > Ship - > Run an apache instance running tomcat
Use case 4 : Build - > Ship - > Run an JDK instance and print "hello World"
Use case 5 : Build - > Ship : Build a custom image contains CENTS OS, JDK 1.7 and Tomcat 7
Use case 6 : Run : Run custom image  which was build.
Use case 7 : Introduction to docker compose and how you can run compose
Use case 8 : Introduction to docker swarm and how to run clusters using docker.
